What cybersecurity risks did you identify in your own digital habits? 
In my daily digital activities, I identified several cybersecurity risks. One of the main risks was using passwords that were easy to remember but not always strong enough. I also realized that I sometimes use the same password pattern across different accounts, which can increase the risk if one account is compromised. Another risk is clicking on links or downloading files without thoroughly checking their source. Public Wi-Fi networks and sharing personal information online can also expose users to cyber threats such as phishing attacks, malware, and data theft.

What security improvements will you implement immediately? 
To improve my security immediately, I will start using strong and unique passwords for every important account. These passwords will include a combination of uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters. I will also enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) on all accounts that support it, including my email, social media, and GitHub accounts. In addition, I will regularly update my operating system and software to ensure that security vulnerabilities are patched. I will be more careful when opening emails, clicking links, or downloading attachments from unknown sources. Using antivirus software and regularly backing up important files are other security measures I plan to follow.

Why is cybersecurity important in today's world? 
Cybersecurity is extremely important in today's world because most personal, academic, and financial activities are conducted online. People use digital platforms for banking, communication, shopping, education, and work. Cyberattacks can result in financial losses, identity theft, privacy violations, and loss of important data. As technology continues to advance, cyber threats are becoming more sophisticated. Therefore, understanding cybersecurity and following safe online practices are essential for protecting personal information, maintaining privacy, and ensuring a secure digital environment for individuals and organizations.
